## Sheet 1: AI - Staff Time Entry
**Doc ID:** `1ViCXRwADPNRfRq0v1vk_Pxr2bPcPPlt2wt4JuMRoTKA`
**Purpose:** Internal staff time logging. Every hour any team member works on a client site is entered here. This is the operational data source for both payroll visibility and client billing calculations.

### Tab Structure

**Time Entry** — The primary data entry tab. Staff log work here in real time.
- Columns: Date, Staff Name, Domain, Plan, Tier, Staff Note (auto-populated maintenance indicator), Billable (Yes/No), Duration (hh:mm), Type of Entry (Support or Management), Descriptive Notes (used in client reports), Entry ID, Timestamp
- The Staff Note field is pulled from the Helper tab and displays the maintenance schedule emoji/label for that client (e.g., ✅ Monthly maintenance — proceed, ⛔ Hosting only, 🚫 No maintenance — bill before work, ❓ Semi-annual check)
- Filter views exist per staff member: April, Bryce, Carol, Eric, Jewel, Nicole, Smit

**Monthly Summary** — Aggregated view filtered to a selected month (date-controlled).
- One row per client domain
- Columns: per-staff time subtotals, Total Duration, Billable Duration, Entry Count
- Shows which clients received time that month and how much

**Staff Summary** — Condensed per-staff view for the selected month.
- Shows: Staff Name, Total Hours (decimal), Billable Hours (decimal), Entry Count
- Current active staff: Bryce, Carol, Jewel, Smit

**Live Monthly Client Totals** — Accumulating historical ledger of finalized monthly totals per client.
- Key: `YYYY-MM` month key + client domain (e.g., `2026-03|receptivadx.com`)
- Columns: Month Key, Client, Total Duration, Billable Duration, Entry Count, Hours (decimal), Billable Hours (decimal)
- Grows month over month; never overwritten. This is the data source for balance calculations in the Support Tracker.

**Closed Monthly Client Totals** — Same structure as Live Monthly Client Totals but for inactive clients.

**All Time Entries / All Entries / Archive** — Full historical logs. Read-only reference views.

**Helper** — The lookup/reference backbone of the entire sheet.
- Columns: Client (domain), Plan, Tier, Team (assigned staff), Months (maintenance rotation schedule cycling Jan 2026 → Dec 2027), Maintenance Schedule (verbose label), Staff Note (emoji + label displayed in Time Entry)
- Source of truth for: plan, assigned staff, maintenance type, and what the time entry form displays as context
- All formula lookups in Time Entry pull from this tab

