## Sheet 2: TESTING - New Monthly Support Tracker
**Doc ID:** `1L7oZ0ERUgG593KNuwd1f_v7NoYY4TlutBkdAT00TbhM`
**Purpose:** Client-facing support management and balance tracking. This is the operational dashboard for every client's support relationship — plans, balances, billing model, contacts, and monthly reporting.

> Note: The "TESTING" prefix indicates this is an in-development version. The structure is largely production-ready but actively evolving.

### Tab Structure

**Instructions** — Overview of how the spreadsheet works, monthly checklist tasks, and payment portal links (Stripe credit card update link, Anchor login).

**Client Directory** — The canonical client registry. One row per client.
- Columns: Client (domain), Plan Type, Email, Status (Active/Inactive/Transitioning), Partner Agency, First/Last Name, Track Time Entry (Yes/No), Payment System (Stripe or Anchor), Renewal Term (Monthly or Annual), Date Updated, Start/End Date, Access to GA, Domain Expiry, Report Folder URL, Monthly Support Doc Link, Special Update Process flag, Asana Project Link, Host, Plan Tier, Staff Note, Maintenance Schedule
- Payment systems: Stripe (monthly billing) or Anchor (annual contracts)
- Host types: WPEngine - RadU Account, WPEngine - Client Account, Hostinger, Kinsta, GoDaddy, Squarespace
- **This is the source of truth for all client metadata.** All other tabs derive from this list.

**Master Tracker 2026** — The rolling monthly balance sheet for the current year. One row per client.
- Columns: Client Name, Status, Transition Notes, Email, First/Last Name, Access to GA, Report Folder URL, Support Doc Link, Internal Notes, Partner Agency, Plan, Old Plan, Active Month, [Current Month — e.g., "Mar 26"], Lookup Key
- The numeric columns for the current month represent: Hours Carried Forward, Hours Used (Billable), Balance, Hours Added (plan refresh), New Balance
- "✔ Added 12 hours" notation = monthly hour allocation applied for managed clients
- Lookup Key format: `YYYY-MM|client.domain` — the join key linking to the Staff Time Entry sheet
- Inactive and Transitioning clients remain in the tracker for historical continuity; they simply don't receive hour additions

**Master - Bucket Model** — A parallel view to Master Tracker 2026 with identical current data. A staging/comparison model for a block/bucket billing approach.

**Feb 2026 / Legacy Monthly Tabs** — Historical monthly snapshots (e.g., "🥂Jan26Tracker", "🎄(LOCKED) Dec25 Tracker", etc.). Locked tabs must not be edited.

**Time Entry** (Support Tracker version) — Legacy manual time entry tab with weekly columns (Week 1–5) per client row. Being phased out in favor of the Staff Time Entry sheet. A note inside reads: "I edited column O and used it to paste in data from my new tracker this month (Feb 2026)."

**Time Import** — Import destination for migrating time data into the new structure.

**Hosting Only** — Clients on hosting-only plans with no support time tracked.

**Block History** — History of prepaid support hour block purchases per client.

**Plans / Monthly Plan** — Plan definitions and pricing structure.

**Blocks over time** — Tracking of how block balances have changed over time.

